<p class="">I do not see how they could have been fit for mobilisation within a year or two years. In their present entirely unsound condition they would deteriorate rapidly, and it would have taken four to five years after the outbreak of war to meet the kind of mobilisation or emergency to which the right hon. Gentleman referred. I am only strengthened in my view that the right hon. Gentleman has not yet considered this question deeply enough. Take the position of all the five capital ships which are to be scrapped: they would have cost——</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
