<p class="">Before the hon. Gentleman leaves the subject of the Washington Treaty, may I say I agree that that is a good debating point; but today there are no nations possessing navies with whom there can be a treaty to scrap. We have, in fact, done by compulsion with Japan, Germany, Italy and the other countries who were fighting us, what we then had to do by agreement.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
